{
  "openapi": "3.0.3",
  "info": {
    "title": "geoCapture API",
    "description": "<p>\n\t\t\t\t\tThis interface provides different endpoints to integrate geoCapture into your software solutions, \n\t\t\t\t\toffering a variety of functionalities for time-tracking, gps tracking services, disposition, and \n\t\t\t\t\tmany more.<br> \n\t\t\t\t\t<br>\n\t\t\t\t\tTime tracking can be achieved through the generation of stamps using this API. These stamps can be \n\t\t\t\t\tused to record employees' working hours. <br>\n\t\t\t\t\t<br>\n\t\t\t\t\tAuthentication in the geoCapture API is handled by passing the \"apitoken\" as a query parameter.\n\t\t\t\t\tDevelopers must include the \"apitoken\" value in their API requests to authenticate and access \n\t\t\t\t\tthe endpoints.<br>\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<br>\n\t\t\t\t\tThis documentation allows you to try out the different endpoints by entering an API key when you \n\t\t\t\t\tclick on the lock icon or on the Authorize Button.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t<br>\n\t\t\t\t\tThis interface is rate limited. You are able to do 100 requests per minute. Further requests are \n\t\t\t\t\tblocked when the rate limit is reached. You will receive a response with the status 429 \"Too Many\n\t\t\t\t\tRequests\". To ensure optimal performance and avoid hitting this limit, we advise minimizing the \n\t\t\t\t\tnumber of API requests. This approach not only helps in adhering to the rate limit but also enhances \n\t\t\t\t\toverall system efficiency and reliability. Strategies like batch processing, caching, and optimizing \n\t\t\t\t\tdata queries can significantly reduce the number of necessary requests, providing a smoother and \n\t\t\t\t\tmore cost-effective user experience.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t<br>\n\t\t\t\t\tPlease note that the API does not support tracking data input into the system.\n\t\t\t\t\tInstead, it provides endpoints to manage and retrieve data related to tracking, such as GPS records. \n\t\t\t\t\tand beacon data, ensuring proper data security and management within the geoCapture system.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t<br>\n\t\t\t\t\tIn case of questions or errors, please contact our support team at \n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"tel:+49545893666872\">+49 5458 93666872</a> or \n\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"mailto:info@geocaputure.de\">info@geocaputure.de</a>.\n\t\t\t\t</p>",
    "version": "1.1.0",
    "contact": {
      "name": "geoCapture GmbH",
      "url": "https://geocapture.de",
      "email": "support@geocapture.de"
    },
    "x-jentic-source-url": "https://app.geocapture.net/api/help/view"
  },
  "servers": [
    {
      "url": "https://app.geocapture.net/api",
      "description": "geoCapture API"
    }
  ],
