    "/dispo_type/fetch_type": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Disposition|Dispo type"
        ],
        "summary": "Fetch dispo type list.",
        "description": "Dispo types within geoCapture are utilized to establish fundamental settings for tour planning. They define a\nnaming scheme for tours (relevant for batch processing in geoCapture) and set required and non required\nqualifications for the tours planned with this dispo type.\n\nWithin the dispo type, you define districts. Districts in geoCapture are designated areas where specific teams\ncarry out their operations. In addition, you can include additional qualifications for each district. Orders are\nlinked to a dispo type by setting a dispo type within an order type. All orders from the selected\norder types will be available for tour planning within the specified dispatch types. Additionally, optimization\ngoals can be established for tours of this type of disposition. Potential optimization targets for tours might\ninvolve increasing the total number of orders fulfilled within the working hours of a team. Another\npossible objective is to minimize the cost associated with each tour. In adition you can select the type of\nroute planning you want to use: car, truck, pedestrian, or bike.\n\n\nNote that you must use the `/dispo_type/fetch_type_data` endpoint for detailed information, such as the\noptimization goals.",
        "operationId": "Disposition|Dispo type_fetchTypeAction",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "name",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Filters the list of disposition types by name. Supports partial matches (case-insensitive). If not specified, all disposition types are returned.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "offset",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Use this parameter to specify the number of records you want to skip before starting to collect the data from\nthe result set.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "limit",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "The limit parameter defines the maximum number of records that can be retrieved in a single\nAPI request, with a max and default value set at 500 records.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Success Response:",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "allOf": [
                    {
                      "$ref": "#/components/schemas/StandardDispoTypeFetchTypeResponse"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/dispo_type/fetch_type_data": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Disposition|Dispo type"
        ],
        "summary": "Request details for a dispo type.",
        "description": "This endpoint allows you to retrieve details of a dispo type.\nWithin the dispo type, you define districts. Districts in geoCapture are designated areas where specific teams\ncarry out their operations. In addition, you can include additional qualifications for each district.\nOrders are linked to a dispo type by setting a dispo type within an order type.\n\nAll orders from the selected order types will be available for tour planning within the specified dispo types.\nAdditionally, optimization goals can be established for tours of this dispo type. Optimization goals for tours\ncould be to do as many orders as possible in the provided work time of a team. Another goal could be low cost for\na tour. You can select the type of route planning you want to use: car, truck, pedestrian, or bike.",
        "operationId": "Disposition|Dispo type_fetchTypeDataAction",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "id",
            "in": "query",
            "required": true,
            "description": "The internal id of the dispo type. The 'fetch dispo type list' endpoint allows you to retrieve the id of a\nspecific dispo type. This Parameter is required.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Success Response:",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "allOf": [
                    {
                      "$ref": "#/components/schemas/StandardDispoTypeFetchTypeDataResponse"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/dispo_type/fetch_team": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Disposition|Dispo type"
        ],
        "summary": "Fetch dispo team list.",
        "description": "This endpoint allows you to fetch a list of dispo teams.\n\nA dispo team is responsible for executing tours. It consists of a team leader and optional additional team\nmembers. These members are not configured in geoCapture. The team leader plays a crucial role by using a mobile\napplication to view assigned tours, navigate to each destination, carry out orders,  mark them as completed\nand move on to subsequent stops.\n\n\nDispo teams allow administrators to set team qualifications, assign vehicles and schedule working hours for dispo\nteams. Such customization ensures that tasks are allocated to teams based on their qualifications and\navailability, improving operational workflows. By following this approach, the system ensures that dispatch teams\nare utilized efficiently, thus maximizing both operational efficiency and cost-effectiveness.",
        "operationId": "Disposition|Dispo type_fetchTeamAction",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "offset",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Use this parameter to specify the number of records you want to skip before starting to collect the data from\nthe result set. This paramter is optional.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "limit",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "The limit parameter defines the maximum number of records that can be retrieved in a single\nAPI request, with a max and default value set at 500 records. This paramter is optional.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Success Response:",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "allOf": [
                    {
                      "$ref": "#/components/schemas/StandardDispoTypeFetchTeamResponse"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/dispo_type/fetch_qualification": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Disposition|Dispo type"
        ],
        "summary": "Fetch dispo qualification list.",
        "description": "\nThis endpoint allows you to fetch a list of qualifications used for tour planning in geoCapture.\nQualifications are a set of criteria that define the capabilities required of teams or individuals to carry out\nspecific tasks. These could include professional licenses, technical skills, physical abilities, or even\nknowledge of certain geographic areas. In geoCapture, qualifications are used to match the requirements of an\norder with the abilities of the workforce.\n\n\nWhen planning tours a manager or dispatcher uses geoCapture to:<br>\n\n<b>Assign Qualifications to a Team:</b><br>\nTeams are assigned qualifications based on their skills and certifications. This ensures that only\nthose who meet the order requirements are considered for assignment.\n\n<b>Match Orders with Qualified Teams:</b><br>\nWhen an order is planned in a tour, geoCapture filters through the team database to find a match between the\norder's requirements and the qualifications of available teams.",
        "operationId": "Disposition|Dispo type_fetchQualificationAction",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "offset",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Use this parameter to specify the number of records you want to skip before starting to collect the data from\nthe result set.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "limit",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "The limit parameter defines the maximum number of records that can be retrieved in a single\nAPI request, with a max and default value set at 500 records.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Success Response:",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "allOf": [
                    {
                      "$ref": "#/components/schemas/StandardDispoTypeFetchQualificationResponse"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/dispo_type/fetch_district": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Disposition|Dispo type"
        ],
        "summary": "Fetch dispo district list.",
        "description": "This endpoint allows you to fetch a list of districts used in the tour planning.\n\nDistricts in geoCapture help organize and manage orders geographically. They are used to group tasks and\nassignments in specific areas, allowing for more efficient planning and execution of field operations. Orders\nare automatically associated with the correct district based on their geographical location. This automatic\nassignment ensures that orders are managed within their respective areas, streamlining the process of planning\nand executing tasks.",
        "operationId": "Disposition|Dispo type_fetchDistrictAction",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "offset",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "Use this parameter to specify the number of records you want to skip before starting to collect the data from\nthe result set. This paramter is optional.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "limit",
            "in": "query",
            "required": false,
            "description": "The limit parameter defines the maximum number of records that can be retrieved in a single\nAPI request, with a max and default value set at 500 records. This paramter is optional.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Success Response:",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "allOf": [
                    {
                      "$ref": "#/components/schemas/StandardDispoTypeFetchDistrictResponse"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/dispo_qualification/fetch": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Disposition|Qualifications"
        ],
        "summary": "Fetch dispo qualification list.",
        "description": "This endpoint enables you to retrieve a list of dispo qualifications, including the name and the id of the\nretrieved qualifications. To modify or add new qualifications, configuration must be performed in geoCapture.",
        "operationId": "Disposition|Qualifications_fetchAction",
